Description: View, search, organize, and share your news and social media. One inbox for all your stuff.
Full Description: Scruddle simplifies how you view, search, organize, and share your social updates, news, and email. Unlike traditional, curated news, Scruddle allows users to find the news they want to see, then organize those stories and headlines based on their own preferences, with funnels. Users can switch between these funnels freely, based on the type of news and information they want to view, when they want to view it. Moreover, Scruddle integrates with Facebook, Twitter, Tumblr, and LinkedIn, to share the stories users have found, as well as allowing updates from Facebook, Twitter, and Tumblr to flow into their Scruddle Inbox with other stories and headlines. Scruddle is free to use, providing social profile integration, news subscriptions, and even custom news feeds and email. Scruddle Premium is a paid subscription, offering more features and benefits, and removing ads from the apps and website. Scruddle was launched as a public beta in 2013, with the public website launch in 2014. Scruddle Inbox for Android was released for Google Play in August 2016, and Scruddle Inbox for iOS was released on the Apple App Store in November 2016.

FreeGate's turnkey Internet systems provide quick-to-implement, reliable secure Internet access for small businesses in a very low cost package. FreeGate's turnkey Internet systems provide industrial-strength capabilities and product features that were only available to large businesses before. With critical Internet features like web server, e-mail, integrated firewall, integrated router, file transfer, and remote management small businesses can operate as BIG businesses on the Net. Full Description: Primera Energy is a Texas-based operator (#677835) with a significant presence in the Eagle Ford Shale and Barnett Shale in Texas. Our commitment and dedication is based around the financial success of our partners along with being environmentally responsible.  Our success can also be attributed to our use of innovative technologies such as top drive rigs, horizontal drilling and multi-stage fracking using state-of-the-art proppants.  This strategy has proven to be the most effective method for drilling shale.  Our guiding principles Our company's vision is guided by the principles of: Financial success of our partners Enduring relationships with our partners Passion and integrity in work Health and safety of employees Protection of the environment   What we have to offer Opportunities for investors to be a direct participant in the Eagle Ford Shale Opportunity to work directly with a Bonded Texas Operator with no middle men  Over 50 years combined  experience in oil and gas exploration and recovery Use of the latest technologies We use the latest technologies such as: top drive rigs horizontal drilling  multi-stage fracking sophisticated proppants History of Primera's Screaming Eagle Wells We gave our wells the unique moniker, “Screaming Eagle,” in honor of the 101st Airborne Division of the United States Army. Founded in 1942, the Screaming Eagles air assault division served in World War II during Operation Overlord and Battle of the Bulge. The Screaming Eagles also played a significant role in the Vietnam War and have also been active in Iraq and Afghanistan. The Screaming Eagles are one of the most decorated units in the U.S. Army, receiving multiple Meritorious Unit Commedations, Presidential Unit Citations, and the Henry Knox Award for Field Artillery Battery. An avid supporter of the San Antonio community, Primera Energy shows that the “Screaming Eagle” wells honor the commitment and sacrifice of the 101st Airborne Division. Primera Energy supports the families of our troops and honor those who gave their lives while bravely defending the principles of freedom and justice.
